The police are hunting for a man who allegedly killed his eight-year-old son on suspicion that he had stolen his Sh1, 000.The 45-year-old man from Mwiitoko sub-location is said to have beaten the boy to death. The man had sold two hens and wanted to use the money for bus fare back to Nairobi where he works.&nbsp;&quot;Even if the father suspected that the child had stolen the money, he should not have killed him,&quot; area sub-chief Phelistus Semo said. &nbsp;&quot;Parents should seek alternative means of disciplining their children.&quot; The body was taken by police to the Dolphin Nursing Home mortuary.